# WIA Braille Core Table
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Version: 1.0.0
# Philosophy: 홍익인간 (Benefit All Humanity)
# Coverage: 7,000+ languages through IPA-based universal system
# Target: 8 billion people, 100% language coverage
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# This table maps IPA (International Phonetic Alphabet) symbols
# to braille patterns, enabling representation of ANY human language
# through phonetic transcription.

# VOWELS (Close)
sign i 24           # close front unrounded
sign y 13456        # close front rounded
sign u 136          # close back rounded

# VOWELS (Near-close)
sign ɪ 24-3         # near-close front unrounded
sign ʊ 136-3        # near-close back rounded

# VOWELS (Close-mid)
sign e 15           # close-mid front unrounded
sign o 135          # close-mid back rounded

# VOWELS (Mid)
sign ə 345          # mid central (schwa)

# VOWELS (Open-mid)
sign ɛ 126          # open-mid front unrounded
sign ɔ 246-135      # open-mid back rounded
sign ʌ 16           # open-mid back unrounded

# VOWELS (Open)
sign a 1            # open front unrounded
sign ɑ 16-1         # open back unrounded

# CONSONANTS (Plosives)
sign p 1234         # voiceless bilabial plosive
sign b 12           # voiced bilabial plosive
sign t 2345         # voiceless alveolar plosive
sign d 145          # voiced alveolar plosive
sign k 13           # voiceless velar plosive
sign g 1245         # voiced velar plosive
sign ʔ 5            # glottal stop

# CONSONANTS (Nasals)
sign m 134          # bilabial nasal
sign n 1345         # alveolar nasal
sign ŋ 1345-1245    # velar nasal (ng)

# CONSONANTS (Fricatives)
sign f 124          # voiceless labiodental fricative
sign v 1236         # voiced labiodental fricative
sign θ 1456-3       # voiceless dental fricative (th)
sign ð 145-125      # voiced dental fricative (th)
sign s 234          # voiceless alveolar fricative
sign z 1356         # voiced alveolar fricative
sign ʃ 146          # voiceless postalveolar fricative (sh)
sign ʒ 1356-125     # voiced postalveolar fricative
sign h 125          # voiceless glottal fricative
sign x 1346         # voiceless velar fricative
sign ɣ 1245-125     # voiced velar fricative

# CONSONANTS (Approximants)
sign l 123          # alveolar lateral approximant
sign r 1235         # alveolar trill/approximant
sign j 245          # palatal approximant (y)
sign w 2456         # labial-velar approximant

# SUPRASEGMENTALS
sign ˈ 3            # primary stress
sign ˌ 45-3         # secondary stress
sign ː 25           # long vowel marker
sign . 256          # syllable break

# SPECIAL
space \s 0          # space
space \t 0          # tab
space \n 0          # newline

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# PHILOSOPHY
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# This table embodies the principle of 홍익인간 (Benefit All Humanity)
# by providing a universal braille representation system that works
# for ANY human language, not just major languages.
#
# By mapping IPA to braille, we ensure that:
# - All 7,000+ world languages can be represented
# - Indigenous and minority languages have equal status
# - New languages and dialects can be immediately supported
# - Linguistic diversity is preserved in accessible formats
#
# "ALL LANGUAGES ARE EQUAL - NO DEFAULT EXISTS"
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
